# Mock Services & Local Dev Rules

## Mock Toggle Pattern
Every external service must check its mock flag at the top of the function. Mocks must produce realistic output — not just `return {}`.

```python
# Standard pattern for all services with external dependencies

async def send_emergency_contact_sos(
    contact_phone: str,
    person_name: str,
    lat: float,
    lng: float,
) -> None:
    if settings.MOCK_SMS:
        logger.info(
            f"[MOCK SMS → {contact_phone}] "
            f"SOS from {person_name} at https://maps.google.com/?q={lat},{lng}"
        )
        return
    # real Brevo call below...
```

## Mock Services Reference

### MOCK_FIREBASE=true
Skip Firebase token verification. Accept a special test token format:
```
Authorization: Bearer mock-token-{phone_number}
# e.g. Bearer mock-token-+491700000001
```
Extract phone from token directly. Create/return the matching user.

### MOCK_SMS=true
All SMS functions print to console with [MOCK SMS] prefix instead of
calling Brevo. Includes full message body and recipient (last 4 digits only).
Safe for local dev — no Brevo API key needed.
To test real delivery: set MOCK_SMS=false and provide a valid BREVO_API_KEY.

### MOCK_MAPS=true
Return a realistic fake Directions API response:
```python
MOCK_DIRECTIONS_RESPONSE = {
    "distance_meters": 850,
    "duration_seconds": 607,  # ~10 min walk
    "polyline": "mock_encoded_polyline_string",
    "steps": ["Head north on Hauptstrasse", "Turn right onto Kaiserstrasse"]
}
```

### MOCK_GEMINI=true
Return a realistic hardcoded safety summary without calling the API:
```python
MOCK_GEMINI_RESPONSES = [
    "This area has had some safety incidents in the past month — stay on well-lit streets and keep your phone accessible.",
    "Low incident history in this area — conditions appear normal for this time of day.",
    "A few incidents were reported near here after 9pm — consider staying on busier routes.",
]
# Pick deterministically based on geohash to keep demo consistent
```

### MOCK_PUSH=true
Log the push notification to stdout with `[MOCK PUSH]` prefix. Never makes an
HTTP call to Expo. Returns `True` so the SOS flow proceeds as if delivered.
```python
logger.info(
    "[MOCK PUSH → …%s | shield=%s] %s: %s | data=%s",
    token[-8:],   # last 8 chars only — never log the full token
    shield_id,
    title,
    body,
    data,
)
return True
```
Default for local dev (`MOCK_PUSH=true` in `.env`). Set `MOCK_PUSH=false` to
send real Expo push notifications (requires shields to have registered tokens).

### MOCK_ELEVENLABS=true
Return a hardcoded `wss://` mock URL without calling the ElevenLabs API.
Used for local dev and tests — no real ElevenLabs conversation session is created.
```python
_MOCK_SIGNED_URL = "wss://mock-elevenlabs-url/conversation/mock-session-id"

if settings.mock_elevenlabs:
    logger.info("[MOCK ELEVENLABS] Returning mock signed URL for incident %s", incident_id)
    return _MOCK_SIGNED_URL
```
Default is `MOCK_ELEVENLABS=true`. Set to `false` to get real signed URLs from
the ElevenLabs API (requires valid `ELEVENLABS_API_KEY` and `ELEVENLABS_AGENT_ID`).

## Dev Endpoint Rules
Dev endpoints are ONLY mounted when `APP_ENV=development`. Add this guard in `main.py`:

```python
if settings.APP_ENV == "development":
    from app.routers import dev
    app.include_router(dev.router, prefix="/dev", tags=["dev"])
```

## Seed Data Spec
The `/dev/seed` endpoint must produce a consistent, demo-ready state:

```python
HEILBRONN_CENTER = (49.1427, 9.2109)

SEED_SHIELDS = [
    {"name": "Anna K.", "phone": "+491700000002", "offset": (0.003, 0.002)},   # ~350m
    {"name": "Sarah M.", "phone": "+491700000003", "offset": (-0.004, 0.001)},  # ~450m
    {"name": "Lisa W.", "phone": "+491700000004", "offset": (0.001, -0.005)},   # ~500m
    {"name": "Maria R.", "phone": "+491700000005", "offset": (0.008, 0.003)},   # ~900m
    {"name": "Julia S.", "phone": "+491700000006", "offset": (-0.006, -0.004)}, # ~720m
]

SEED_PERSON = {"name": "Test Person", "phone": "+491700000001"}

SEED_INCIDENTS = [
    # Past incidents for hotspot data — same geohash area
    {"lat": 49.1431, "lng": 9.2115, "hour": 22},
    {"lat": 49.1419, "lng": 9.2098, "hour": 23},
    {"lat": 49.1440, "lng": 9.2120, "hour": 21},
]
```

Seed must be **idempotent** — running it twice should not create duplicates. Use `ON CONFLICT DO UPDATE` or check existence first.

## Test SOS Flow Helper
`/dev/trigger-test-sos` simulates a full SOS sequence for demo purposes:

1. Trigger SOS at Heilbronn center as the seed Person
2. Auto-respond with the 3 closest seed Shields (mock response — no real push)
3. Calculate and return convergence point
4. Return full incident state ready for frontend demo

This endpoint must work with `MOCK_SMS=true` and `MOCK_MAPS=true` — no real API calls.

## Shield Movement Simulator
`/dev/mock-shield-respond/{incident_id}/{shield_id}` moves a shield 10% closer to convergence on each call. Used to simulate live navigation in the demo:

```python
# Move shield 10% of remaining distance toward convergence point
new_lat = shield_lat + (convergence_lat - shield_lat) * 0.1
new_lng = shield_lng + (convergence_lng - shield_lng) * 0.1
```

Call this in a loop from the frontend demo script to animate shield movement.

## Logging in Dev Mode
When `APP_ENV=development`, increase log verbosity:
- Log all incoming requests with method, path, and user_id
- Log all Redis reads/writes (key + operation, never value)
- Log mock service calls with `[MOCK]` prefix
- Log convergence point recalculations with before/after coordinates
